<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320FFFF75CF70375FDEBFC64" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CF70375FDEBFC64" blockId="1.[174,1233,779,934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
D i a g n o s i s.The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF75E140372FD9FFCE7" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[512,619,779,805]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75E140372FD9FFCE7" box="[512,619,779,805]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF75F550372FC4AFCE7" authorityName="E.Newman" authorityYear="1834" box="[833,958,779,805]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eristalinae">Eristalinae</taxonomicName>
genera by the following combination of characters: eye with rim along the facial border; face in both sexes with well-defined facial knob and mouth edge, arista dorsal and hair-like; wing with vein R 
<subScript id="1122A91C320FFFF758A20327FB24FCAE" attach="left" box="[1206,1232,862,876]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">4+5</subScript>
straight, crossvein r-m before middle of discal cell; blackish species, abdomen oval, parallelsided, rarely with grayish spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320FFFF75CBA03C3FD7AFC0D" box="[174,654,953,975]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA03C3FD7AFC0D" blockId="1.[174,654,953,975]" box="[174,654,953,975]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<heading id="D6511C35320FFFF75CBA03C3FD7AFC0D" box="[174,654,953,975]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" reason="5">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75CBA03C3FD7AFC0D" bold="true" box="[174,654,953,975]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
Key to the Iranian species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF75E2603C0FD7AFC0D" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[562,654,953,975]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75E2603C0FD7AFC0D" bold="true" box="[562,654,953,975]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320FFFF45CBA039DFB3DFE88" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="key">
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA039DFB25FBD7" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA039DFB25FC38" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,996,1018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA039DFB25FC38" box="[174,1233,996,1018]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">1. Eye bare or with small and sparse hairs. ............................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0386FB25FBD7" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,1023,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0386FB25FBD7" box="[174,1233,1023,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">— Eyes haired. ............................................................................................................................................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA0460FB25FBA7" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0460FB24FB88" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0460FB24FB88" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
2. Legs black, at most tibia pale basally; sternites 2–5 shiny, often in contrast to a dull sternite 1; genitalia as in 
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320FFFF75CE0044DFED0FB88" box="[244,292,1076,1098]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[180,1228,1180,1709]" captionTargetId="figure-448@4.[166,1229,1184,1709]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Cheilosia mutabilis (a–c): a — dorsal view of male, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. nigrips, male (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — lateral view of head; f — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449153/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75D3A044DFEC1FB8B" box="[302,309,1076,1097]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">f</emphasis>
. ................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF75878044CFB24FB88" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1132,1232,1077,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75878044CFB24FB88" box="[1132,1232,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0436FB25FBA7" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,1103,1125]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0436FB25FBA7" box="[174,1233,1103,1125]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">— Legs partly pale at least tibia pale at the both ends. ............................................................................................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA0410FB25FB58" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0410FB25FBBD" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,1129,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0410FB25FBBD" box="[174,1233,1129,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">3. Arista bare or shorthaired, hairs shorter than basal diameter of arista. ........................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA04FDFB25FB58" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,1156,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA04FDFB25FB58" box="[174,1233,1156,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">— Arista with hairs longer than the diameter of thickend basal part of arista. ................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA04E6FB25FB0D" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA04E6FB24FB76" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1232,1183,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA04E6FB24FB76" box="[174,1232,1183,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
4. Hind margin of scutellum without bristle. ........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF7584904E6FB24FB76" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" box="[1117,1232,1183,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF7584904E6FB24FB76" box="[1117,1232,1183,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. laticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA04C0FB25FB0D" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1233,1209,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA04C0FB25FB0D" box="[174,1233,1209,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">— Hind margin of scutellum with bristle. ................................................................................................................. 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA04ADFB24FAC7" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA04ADFB24FB2B" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1232,1236,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA04ADFB24FB2B" box="[174,1232,1236,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
5. Third antennal segment more than 3 times as long as second segment (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320FFFF75F9504ADFC45FB28" box="[897,945,1236,1258]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75FA804ADFC3CFB2B" box="[956,968,1236,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">h</emphasis>
). ................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF7588704ACFB24FB2B" authorityName="Zimina" authorityYear="1970" box="[1171,1232,1236,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lola">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF7588704ACFB24FB2B" box="[1171,1232,1236,1258]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. lola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0496FB24FAC7" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" box="[174,1232,1263,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0496FB24FAC7" box="[174,1232,1263,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
— Third antennal segment less than 3 times as long as second segment (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320FFFF75F640496FC54FAC7" box="[880,928,1263,1285]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75FBF0496FC46FAC6" box="[939,946,1263,1284]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">f</emphasis>
). ......................... 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF7584D0496FB24FAC7" authorityName="Szilady" authorityYear="1938" box="[1113,1232,1263,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cumanica">
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF7584D0496FB24FAC7" box="[1113,1232,1263,1285]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">C. cumanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3652B3FC320FFFF75CBA0570FB25FA97" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320FFFF75CBA0570FB24FAFB" blockId="1.[174,1233,996,1845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="3657086C320FFFF75CBA0570FB24FAFB" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
6. Facial knob slender, in male nearly triangular, in female only occupying 1/3 of the face viewed from above (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320FFFF75CF6055DFEE6FAF8" box="[226,274,1316,1338]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320FFFF75D09055DFEDDFAFB" box="[285,297,1316,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">b</emphasis>
). ................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4AA6D0DA320FFFF75848055CFB24FAFB" baseAuthorityName="Fallien" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[1116,1232,1316,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
